title: Indian killed in Ukraine: ‘He stayed back to help juniors… died when he went to get food’ - The Indian Express
content:
1. Indian killed in Ukraine: ‘He stayed back to help juniors… died when he went to get food’  The Indian Express
  2. Indian Student Killed In Shelling In Ukraine's Kharkiv  NDTV
  3. Indian student Naveen Gyanagoudar was waiting to buy food when he was killed in shelling in Ukraine  Economic Times
  4. 1st Indian Fatality; Tragedy Strikes In Kharkiv, Naveen Lost Life When He Went Outside To Get Supply  India Today
  5. ‘How do I explain (to my family) that even going out for groceries is game of life and death’  The Indian Express
  6. View Full coverage on Google News
description: Naveen S G, a 21-year-old fourth-year medical student from Karnataka, stepped out of the bunker, where the students had been holed up for the past six days, to buy groceries -- and became the first Indian casualty in Russia's invasion of Ukraine.
